</paragraph>
<caption id="08AE44891DB3C945B3B71AB77DBADA61" ID-Zenodo-Dep="974209" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure85" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96443" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" start="Figure 85" startId="F85">
<paragraph id="A33E4C225028E60B7BCA27AFE6DE15B6" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis id="12565010BE65E2E7699C43AD9E9060C7" bold="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Figure 85.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="E16E1E1763E9E21A0AC2A922B408AA4B" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lindenii" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindenii">
<emphasis id="AC01FEE29E84FABFE4F8BD7F28CB0600" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia lindenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="07D8552A777F4A8CCB4696475304DF71" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Note that in Dominican Republic a pubescent morphotype of 
<taxonomicName id="FACADF60BC52D90B653621EF785CD8B0" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia superba" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis id="4B5E9870DDCFFD83101B020B3E05AD77" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected in the same place. They are similar but when looking at the flower buds, 
<taxonomicName id="38F077C653685FA8A1ACB469F7255B29" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lindenii" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lindenii">
<emphasis id="CAB0C3DFFF0B4D07528F45FC12C83B5E" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia lindenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has pubescent buds with the lobes somewhat evident in the calyptra apex. In 
<taxonomicName id="E375018EDCF6A85B8B2F6D7BF4C2B255" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia superba" order="Myrtales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis id="1F38B5985A167AFF296A697F4583FCCC" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Conostegia superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the other hand, the flower bud and calyptra are glabrous and the lobes not discernible at all.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
